    "content": "Lea, quick update from my contrast audit with Steve Schoger. One finding that affects the CSS tokens:\n\n**`--color-success` (oklch 0.55 0.15 145) fails WCAG AA for normal text** at ~3.9:1. It passes for large text (3:1) and UI components.\n\nThe fix options:\n1. Darken to L=0.50 or lower (would need Steve's approval on the visual)\n2. Add a CSS comment restricting usage: \"Use for icons and large indicators only. Not for normal-sized text.\"\n3. Add a darker variant: `--color-success-dark: oklch(0.45 0.15 145)` for any text use\n\nI'd recommend option 2 for now -- we're using green for completed-state indicators (checkmarks, strikethrough styling), not for text messages. Steve already confirmed completed todos will use strikethrough + color, not color alone.\n\nAlso, I've reiterated the `--color-fg-muted` recommendation: bump from gray-500 to gray-600. It's 4.6:1 right now -- technically passing but one rounding error away from failure. Gray-600 gives 7.4:1, which is comfortable."
  }
